30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30cd\u30eb\uff3d}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Accolades ==\nLove Yourself tour was nominated for three awards during ticket sale website [[Ticketmaster]]'s year-end awards, winning two of them. The Ticket of the Year Award was awarded to BTS following a user poll by Ticketmaster, using a database of roughly 200&nbsp;million people to determine the most popular touring act of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=BTS win Ticketmaster\u2019s ticket of the year 2018|url=https://www.iq-mag.net/2018/11/bts-ticketmaster-ticket-of-the-year-2018/#.XG1nThuWw5s|website=IQ|accessdate=February 20, 2019|date=November 28, 2018}}</ref> In addition, BTS was awarded the French ticket of the year award, which pulled from data via French Ticketmaster sales. The tour was also nominated for the \"Most Anticipated Event of the Year, 2019\" award, but did not receive it.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ticketmaster : le boys band cor\u00e9en BTS \u00e9lu par les fans Ticket of the Year 2018|url=https://www.morenoconseil.com/ticketmaster-le-boys-band-coreen-bts-elu-par-les-fans-ticket-of-the-year-2018/|website=morenconciel|accessdate=March 12, 2019|language=French|date=November 27, 2018}}</ref> Love Yourself also won the grand prize award at the 6th Edaily Culture Awards for Best Concert. The Seoul performances were popular among judges because, according to Kim Eun-koo of ''Edaily'', they \"created a new history [for] K-pop\". The skill of the performers and popularity of the event were also cited as influences on the decision.<ref>{{cite web|title=[\ubb38\ud654\ub300\uc0c1 \ucd5c\uc6b0\uc218\uc791]\u2461 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 '\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \ub7ec\ube0c \uc720\uc5b4\uc140\ud504'|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=018&aid=0004298041&sid1=001|work=Edaily|accessdate=January 23, 2019|language=Korean|date=January 24, 2019|last=Kim|first=Eun-koo}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[American Music Awards of 2019|47th Annual American Music Awards]], Love Yourself World Tour was awarded the \"[[American Music Award for Tour of the Year|Tour of the Year]]\" award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8544611/2019-amas-winners-list|title=Here Are All the Winners From the 2019 American Music Awards|last=Warner|first=Denise|date=November 24, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125043916/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8544611/2019-amas-winners-list|archive-date=November 25, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=November 25, 2019}}</ref> The tour was also nominated for Ticketmaster's 2019 UK ticket of the year and Global ticket of the year awards,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iq-mag.net/2019/11/pink-ticketmaster-global-ticket-of-the-year-2019/|title=Pink named TM\u2019s global Ticket of the Year 2019|date=2019-11-20|website=IQ Magazine|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> while it won the France ticket of the year, Most Anticipated Event of the Year 2020 in France and in Spain awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mgbmag.fr/2019/11/21/communique-bts-remporte-le-trophee-ticket-of-the-year-de-ticketmaster-france/|title=[Communiqu\u00e9] BTS remporte le troph\u00e9e Ticket of The Year de Ticketmaster France|last=r\u00e9daction|first=La|website=MGB Mag|language=fr-FR|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.es/cultura/musica/abci-metallica-mejor-concierto-2019-espana-201911201310_noticia.html|title=Metallica, el mejor concierto de 2019 en Espa\u00f1a|date=2019-11-20|website=abc|language=es|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref>\n\n===Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Year \n! scope=\"col\"| Organization \n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! class=\"unsortable\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2019\n| align=\"center\"| Edaily Culture Awards{{efn|The Edaily Culture Awards are a South Korean award ceremony established in 2019 to honor the year's best achievements in six categories: theatre, classical, dance, Korean music, musicals and concerts. Winners are selected by a panel of 54 judges who are professionals in each field.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=01154566622394784&mediaCodeNo=257|script-title=ko:[\uc81c6\ud68c\uc774\ub370\uc77c\ub9ac\ubb38\ud654\ub300\uc0c1]\u2463 \uc5ed\ub300 \ub300\uc0c1 \uc218\uc0c1\uc791\uc740?|last=Lee|first=Yun-jung|date=February 27, 2019|work=EDaily|language=ko|trans-title=[The 6th Annual EDaily Culture Awards] What is the best award?|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190227033636/https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=01154566622394784&mediaCodeNo=257|archive-date=February 27, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mk.co.kr/news/entertain/view/2019/02/115385/|script-title=ko:[MK\uc774\uc288] \u201c\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8, \ub300\uc0c1 \uc601\uc608 \uc548\uc744\uae4c\u201d...\ubb38\ud654\ub300\uc0c1, \uc624\ub298(26\uc77c) \uac1c\ucd5c|date=February 26, 2019|last=Lee|first=Da-kyeom|work=EDaily|language=ko|trans-title=[MK Issue] \"BTS, honored to win the award\" ... Culture Grand Prize, held today (26th)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709233836/https://www.mk.co.kr/news/entertain/view/2019/02/115385/|archive-date=July 9, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=August 5, 2019|via=MK}}</ref>}}\n| align=\"center \"|Concert Category\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:[\uc885\ud569IS] '\ubb38\ud654\ub300\uc0c1' \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8, \ub300\uc0c1\uae4c\uc9c0 2\uad00\uc655 \"\ud55c\uad6d \ubb38\ud654 \ub354 \uc804\ud30c\ud560 \uac83\"|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002885118|last=Kim|first=Yeon-ji|date=February 26, 2019|work=Daily Sports|language=ko|trans-title=[ComprehensiveIS] 'Cultural Daesang' BTS, 2-time winner, \"We will spread Korean culture more\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190226234139/https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002885118|archive-date=February 26, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=July 12, 2019|via=[[Naver (corporation)|Naver]]}}</ref>\n|-\n\n| align=\"center\"|[[American Music Awards of 2019|2019]]\n| align=\"center\"| [[American Music Awards]]\n| align=\"center\"| Tour of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{Cite web|url=    https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/24/entertainment/amas-2019-winners-list/index.html       |title=  American Music Awards winners announced|website=cnn.com| archive-date=November 25, 2019|url-status=live|accessdate=November 25, 2019 }}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* ''[[Love Yourself in Seoul]]'' \u2014 film of the concert held at the Jamsil Olympic Stadium\n* ''[[Bring the Soul: The Movie]]'' \u2014 interview with the BTS members about the Love Yourself tour\n* ''Bring the Soul: Docu-series'' \u2014 similar as the [[Bring the Soul: The Movie|film]] in episodic format, interview with the BTS members about the Love Yourself tour\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{BTS}}\n\n[[Category:2018 concert tours]]\n[[Category:2019 concert tours]]\n[[Category:BTS concert tours]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018\u201319 concert tour by BTS}}\n{{Infobox concert tour\n| concert_tour_name = BTS World Tour: Love Yourself\n| image             = BTS World Tour Love Yourself logo.png\n| landscape         = yes\n| artist            = [[BTS (band)|BTS]]\n| gross             = $71.77+ million{{efn|The total is only an accumulation of the 18 dates with publicly available box office data and does not reflect the total gross of the tour.}}\n| attendance        = 1.02 million\n| type              = World\n| album             = ''[[Love Yourself: Her]]''<br/> ''[[Love Yourself: Tear]]''<br/> ''[[Love Yourself: Answer]]''<br/> ''[[Face Yourself]]''\n| start_date        = {{startdate|2018|8|25}}\n| end_date          = {{startdate|2019|4|7}}{{efn|The \"Love Yourself\" section of the tour ended on April 7, 2019, however a separately named extension, called BTS World Tour Love Yourself: Speak Yourself, was eventually added.<ref name=\"SYextension\" />}}\n| number_of_legs    = 8\n| number_of_shows   = {{unbulleted list| 20 in Asia|15 in North America|7 in Europe|42 in Total}} \n| last_tour         = [[The Wings Tour|2017 BTS Live Trilogy Episode III: The Wings Tour]]<br/>(2017)\n| this_tour         = '''BTS World Tour: Love Yourself'''<br/>(2018-2019)\n| next_tour         = [[Love Yourself World Tour#Speak Yourself extension|BTS World Tour Love Yourself: Speak Yourself]]<br/>(2019)\n}}\n\n'''BTS World Tour: Love Yourself''', commonly known as the '''Love Yourself World Tour''', was the third worldwide [[concert tour]] headlined by South Korean band [[BTS (band)|BTS]] to promote their ''Love Yourself'' series, including their ''[[Love Yourself: Her]]'' EP, ''[[Love Yourself: Tear]]'' studio album, and ''[[Love Yourself: Answer]]'' compilation album.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8390251/bts-announce-new-tour-dates-full-list|title=BTS Announces World Tour With Stops In Six North American Cities|work=Billboard|accessdate=April 26, 2018}}</ref> The tour began on August 25, 2018 in South Korea. A stadium extension to the tour, titled '''BTS World Tour Love Yourself: Speak Yourself''', was added on February 9, 2019 and began in [[Pasadena, California]] on May 4, 2019. The tour concluded on October 29, 2019, comprising 62 concerts in 14 countries.<ref>{{cite web|title=Love Yourself BTS World Tour|url=http://bts.ibighit.com/btsworldtour/ |website=ibighit|publisher=Big Hit Entertainment|accessdate=March 1, 2019}}</ref> The Love Yourself World Tour ranked at number three on ''Billboard''<nowiki/>'s 2019 Year End Top 40 Tours chart worldwide, with a worldwide gross of $196.4 million from the last 42 shows of the tour. In total, the tour was attended by 2,019,800 people, becoming BTS' most successful tour to date and the highest grossing concert tour by an act that performs primarily in a non-English language reported by ''Billboard''.\n\n== Background ==\nOn April 26, 2018, [[Big Hit Entertainment]] released a trailer on their official [[YouTube]] channel announcing an upcoming world tour.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rN4_GOtBoj4|title=BTS (\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8) World Tour \"Love Yourself\" Spot|date=April 26, 2018|work=BigHit Entertainment|accessdate=April 28, 2018}}</ref> The video revealed an initial schedule of 22 concerts across 11 cities worldwide.<ref>\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8390251/bts-announce-new-tour-dates-full-list|title=BTS Announces World Tour With Stops In Six North American Cities|first=Tamar|last=Herman|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 27, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.theo2.co.uk/events/detail/bts|title=BTS World Tour 'Love Yourself'|website=theo2|accessdate=May 27, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bts.ibighit.com/btsworldtour/|title=BTS World Tour|website=bts.ibighit.com|language=ko|accessdate=April 26, 2018}}</ref> After the announcement, multiple hashtags trended worldwide on social media, including the tour's namesake tag\u2014 #LOVE_YOURSELF, highlighting the level of anticipation surrounding the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8390293/bts-tour-army-reaction|title=Army Around the Globe React to BTS' Love Yourself World Tour Announcement|work=Billboard|first=Tamar|last=Herman|date=April 26, 2018|accessdate=May 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Commercial reception ==\nIn May 2018, after the first round of North American ticket pre-sales sold out in seconds,<ref name=\"BTS NA Tour tickets\">{{cite news|url=http://www.powerhouselive.net/event/event_cnt_view.asp?idx=18|title=BTS World Tour 'Love Yourself'|accessdate=May 27, 2018|website=powerhouselive.net}}</ref><ref name=\"BTS NA Tour LA day 4\">{{cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2018/05/06/bts-listen-army-add-extra-date-tour-tickets-sell-seconds-7524733/|title=BTS listen to their Army and add extra date to tour after tickets sell out|date=May 6, 2018|work=Metro|accessdate=May 9, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> a fourth show at Los Angeles' [[Staples Center]] was added to the tour due to overwhelming fan demand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.staplescenter.com/news/detail/love-yourself-bts-brand-new-world-tour-announces-a-4th-la-show-added-due-to-overwhelming-fan-demand|title=LOVE YOURSELF\u2019: BTS\u2019 Brand-New World Tour Announces a 4th LA Show Added Due to Overwhelming Fan Demand|last=|first=|date=2018-05-05|website=Staples Center|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-21}}</ref> Tickets for the Hamilton shows sold out in just over an hour, with organizers for the Ontario stop, [[Culture of Hamilton, Ontario#Core Entertainment|Core Entertainment]], revealing they would have sold out faster if not for the strain put on [[Ticketmaster]]'s online system due to the unprecedented heavy influx of site traffic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804022209/https://www.thespec.com/whatson-story/8595366-rockingham-k-pop-flexes-its-ticket-selling-muscle-at-firstontario-centre/|title=Rockingham: K-pop flexes its ticket selling muscle at FirstOntario Centre {{!}} TheSpec.com|date=August 4, 2018|access-date=August 4, 2018}}</ref> All fourteen North American stops completely sold out,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bryanrolli/2018/05/18/bts-love-yourself-tear-already-broke-records/#6a7a6c1dc7d2|title=BTS Already Broke Records With Their New Album, 'Love Yourself: Tear'|last=Rolli|first=Bryan|date=May 18, 2018|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=May 27, 2018}}</ref> prompting the addition of a fifteenth and final stop of the North American leg at New York's [[Citi Field]]. The concert sold out in under ten minutes,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8470824/bts-citi-field-concert-sold-out|title=BTS' Citi Field Show Sells Out Within Minutes|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=August 17, 2018|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=August 25, 2018}}</ref> making BTS the first Korean artist to headline a stadium show in the United States.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=109&aid=0003839759|access-date=August 9, 2018|language=ko|script-title=ko:[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8, 10\uc6d4 \u7f8e \uc2a4\ud0c0\ub514\uc6c0 \uacf5\uc5f0 \ud655\uc815 '\ud55c\uad6d\uac00\uc218 \ucd5c\ucd08'}}</ref> The London, Amsterdam, Berlin, and Paris arena stops, marking the group's first and biggest headlining shows in Europe at the time,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/whats-on/music-nightlife-news/bts-announce-london-o2-arena-14583434|title=BTS announce London O2 Arena shows on world tour \u2013 how to get tickets|last=Yates|first=Jonathon|date=April 27, 2018|website=getwestlondon|accessdate=May 27, 2018}}</ref> also met commercial success with the London dates selling out in two minutes and the Berlin shows selling out in nine minutes.<ref>* {{cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/06/01/bts-army-fury-tickets-london-dates-resold-nearly-2000-minutes-selling-7596543/|title=BTS Army fury as tickets for London dates are resold for nearly \u00a32,000 minutes after selling out|last=Kelly|first=Emma|date=June 1, 2018|work=Metro|accessdate=June 1, 2018}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.yonhapnews.co.kr/bulletin/2018/06/01/0200000000AKR20180601181300082.HTML?input=1195m|date=June 1, 2018|work=Yonhap News Agency|language=ko|script-title=ko:\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \ubca0\ub97c\ub9b0 \uacf5\uc5f0\ud2f0\ucf13 3\ub9cc\uc7a5 9\ubd84\ub9cc\uc5d0 \ub9e4\uc9c4|accessdate=June 1, 2018}}</ref> After the second general sale for Seoul's [[Seoul Olympic Stadium]] dates opened in August, all 90,000 available tickets sold out.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=117&aid=0003087372|access-date=August 6, 2018|language=ko|script-title=ko:\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8, 'Love Yourself' \uc11c\uc6b8 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \ud2f0\ucf13 \uc624\ud508\uacfc \ub3d9\uc2dc 9\ub9cc \uc804\uc11d \ub9e4\uc9c4!}}</ref> Estimated to have sold a total of 790,000 tickets from 33 sold out shows in 16 cities,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportalkorea.com/butterfly/view.php?gisa_uniq=201810070909779780|website=sportalkorea.com|language=Korean|script-title=ko:\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \ub274\uc695 \uc2dc\ud2f0\ud544\ub4dc \uacf5\uc5f0, \uc0dd\uc0dd\ud55c \ud604\uc7a5 \uc911\uacc4 [\uc18d\ubcf4|accessdate=October 10, 2018}}</ref> BTS added eight additional Asia dates while touring the European leg of the tour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.koreaportal.com/articles/46223/20181010/bts-announces-new-asia-tour-dates-guinness-world-records-subtly-sends-cup-of-tea-invite-to-k-pop-idols.htm|title=BTS Announces New Asia Tour Dates; Guinness World Records Subtly Sends \"Cup Of Tea\" Invite To K-Pop Idols|last=Rapir|first=Jessica|date=2018-10-10|website=Korea Portal|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-21}}</ref> The first [[K-pop]] artists to play at Singapore's [[National Stadium, Singapore|National Stadium]], tickets sold out in less than four hours.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/tickets-for-bts-concert-at-national-stadium-sell-out-in-less-than-4-hours|title=Tickets for BTS concert at National Stadium sell out in less than 4 hours|last1=Wong|first1=Derek|date=October 27, 2018|website=The Straights Times|accessdate=March 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ticket resale site [[StubHub]], BTS was one of 2018's best selling live artists in international markets outside the United States, second to only [[Ed Sheeran]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=McDermott |first1=Maeve |title=2018's best-selling live artists are Ed Sheeran, Bruce Springsteen and BTS, per Stubhub |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2018/12/04/2018-s-best-selling-live-artists-ed-sheeran-bruce-springsteen-bts/2204203002/ |website=[[USA Today]] |accessdate=December 4, 2018 |date=December 4, 2018}}</ref> ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' named BTS as one of the top touring acts of Fall 2018 in the [[United States]], entering StubHub's \"highest-selling act\" and \"best-selling shows\" lists with the \"highest-selling average sales per show position\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/news/elton-john-bts-lead-stubhubs-top-u-s-fall-tours-1202929132/|title=Elton John, BTS Lead StubHub\u2019s Top U.S. Fall Tours|date=September 6, 2018|website=Variety|access-date=September 6, 2018}}</ref> According to [[Yahoo! Finance|''Yahoo!'' Finance]], BTS were also the top-selling act and top-selling show in [[Canada]] for Fall 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/stubhub-announces-top-10-canada-110000674.html|title=StubHub Announces Top-10 Canada Tours This Fall: BTS Takes #1 Position as K-pop Conquers Canada|last=CNW Group|first=|date=September 12, 2018|work=Yahoo Finance|access-date=September 12, 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190503141700/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/stubhub-announces-top-10-canada-110000674.html|archive-date=2019-05-03|language=en-US}}</ref> In Japan, BTS came in as the nineteenth best-selling touring act on ''Nikkei Entertainment''<nowiki/>'s 2018 Concert Mobilization Ranking Top 50.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gwak |first1=Hyeon-soo |script-title=ko:\ub3d9\ubc29\uc2e0\uae30, \u65e5 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \ub3d9\uc6d0\ub825 1\uc704\u2026\uc544\ub77c\uc2dc-\uc544\ubb34\ub85c\ub098\ubbf8\uc5d0 \uc81c\uccd0 [\uacf5\uc2dd] |url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=382&aid=0000686198|website=[[Naver]]|accessdate=December 4, 2018|language=Korean|date=November 5, 2018}}</ref> \n\n== Critical reception ==\nThe Love Yourself received positive reviews from critics. For the first concerts in America, local media reported in Los Angeles since the moment fans started to camp outside the ''[[Staples Center]]'' days ahead the concert.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8473745/bts-fans-camp-out-staples-center-los-angeles-video|title=BTS Fans Camp Out at Staples Center Ahead of K-Pop Band's LA Shows: Watch|last=Schiller|first=Rebecca|date=September 5, 2018|work=Billboard|access-date=September 12, 2018}}</ref> Philip Cosores from ''[[Uproxx]]'' described BTS' Staples Center 4 night concerts as \"Enormous, multi-sensory experience\" bringing an \"Inclusive\" and \"Multicultural experience\" where music is above any language barrier.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://uproxx.com/music/bts-los-angeles-concert-review-staples-center/|title=Korean Pop Group BTS Paint An Inclusive, Diverse Future For Pop Music|last=Cosores|first=Philip|date=2018-09-12|work=UPROXX|access-date=September 12, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> Tiffany Taylor from ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' noted for ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard News]]'' the \"Amazing choreography\" praising the solo performances and energy of the fans as highlight of the night.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8474544/4-secrets-bts-los-angeles-love-yourself-tour-dates|title=4 Secrets From BTS' Los Angeles 'Love Yourself' Tour Dates: Watch|last=Kelly|first=Tetris|date=September 10, 2008|work=Billboard|access-date=September 12, 2018}}</ref> Jim Harrington from ''[[The Mercury News]]'' referred to the [[Oracle Arena]] concert on [[Oakland, California|Oakland]] as \"the hottest concert of the year in the Bay Area\" noting the solo performances as \"witnessing seven individual stars, each of whom could enjoy a successful solo career.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mercurynews.com/2018/09/12/bts-concert-review-k-pop-phenomenon-hits-bay-area/|title=Review: Does BTS live up to the immense hype in concert? (with set list)|last=Harrington|first=Jim|date=September 12, 2018|work=The Mercury News|access-date=September 14, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> For the Chicago show critic Kim Youngdae stated their strengths were the dazzling group displays, the artistry in the solo numbers, and how immersive it was.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Youngdae|title=[Review] Chicago shows its love for BTS during \"Love Yourself\" tour |url=http://www.hani.co.kr/arti/english_edition/e_entertainment/864761.html|website=www.hani.co.kr|accessdate=October 8, 2018}}</ref> Crystal Bell from [[MTV]] said about the tour, \"BTS have created an experience so captivating, so inclusive, and so visually stunning that it\u2019s cemented the boy band as one of the most vital acts in pop music today.\"<ref name =\"CF1\">{{cite web|last1=Bell|first1=Crystal|title=THE 10 MOST BEAUTIFUL MOMENTS OF BTS\u2019 LOVE YOURSELF TOUR|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3101141/bts-love-yourself-tour-moments-citi-field/|website=www.mtv.com|accessdate=October 9, 2018}}</ref> The Quietus wrote about the European tour as \" The show is about a search for self-identity. After two-and-a-half hours of costume changes, pulsing beats, soaring high notes and the impossible iconic beauty of their videos, BTS walk to the front of the stage in low-key jeans and T-shirts. As they sing the last song, \u2018Anpanman\u2019, which is about a new kind of superhero, we realise that their awkwardness and sensitivity is also the source of their strength.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thequietus.com/articles/25481-three-songs-no-flash-bts-o2-arena|title=The Quietus \u2013 Features \u2013 Three Songs No Flash \u2013 Feel Love, Real Love: BTS at the O2|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe Denisonian rated the concert ten out of ten, stating the music, visuals, dancing, and fans is what made it a great experience.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sferra|first1=Chloe|title=Concert Review: BTS is A Whole New Experience|url=http://www.denisonian.com/2018/11/features/concert-review-bts-is-a-whole-new-experience/|website=The Denisonian|accessdate=December 4, 2018|date=November 18, 2018}}</ref> [[Vivid Seats]] named BTS the 2018 artist of the year, citing the group's history-making concert at [[Citi Field]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 Year In Review: The Year in Live Events|url=https://www.vividseats.com/blog/2018-top-live-events|accessdate=January 2, 2019|date=December 18, 2018|publisher=Vivid Seats}}</ref>\n\n== Setlist ==\nBTS featured three set lists for their concerts. It included the same songs except for the title medley (#12 to #16).<ref>\n*{{cite web|title=BTS 'Love Yourself Tour' In London: Tickets, Dates And Latest Updates And News|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/music/bts-london-o2-tickets-dates-news-setlist/|website=Capitalfm|accessdate=October 15, 2018|date=September 11, 2018}}\n*{{cite web|last1=Martinez |first1=Tara |title=What's The BTS 'Love Yourself' Concert Setlist? Here Are The Songs To Expect In The Film|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/whats-the-bts-love-yourself-concert-setlist-here-are-the-songs-to-expect-in-the-film-15558162 |website=[[Elite Daily]]|accessdate=December 21, 2018|date=December 20, 2018}}</ref>\n<!-- Don't put a hidden template here, per MOS:DONTHIDE -->\n\n{{Col-start}}\n{{Col-2}}\n# \"[[Idol (BTS song)|Idol]]\"\n# \"[[Save Me (BTS song)|Save Me]]\"\n# \"I'm Fine\"\n# \"Magic Shop\"\n# \"Trivia {{lang|ko-Hant|\u8d77}}: Just Dance\"\n# \"[[Euphoria (BTS song)|Euphoria]]\"\n# \"[[I Need U (BTS song)|I Need U]]\"\n# \"[[Run (BTS song)|Run]]\"\n# \"[[Serendipity (BTS song)|Serendipity]]\"\n# \"Trivia {{lang|ko-Hant|\u627f}}: Love\"\n# \"[[DNA (BTS song)|DNA]]\"\n# \"21st Century Girl\u201d{{ref|a|[a]}} / \"Boyz with Fun\"{{ref|b|[b]}}/ \"Dope\"{{Ref|c|[c]}}\n# \"Go Go\"{{ref|a|[a]}}{{Ref|c|[c]}} / \"Attack on Bangtan\"{{ref|b|[b]}}\n# \"[[Blood Sweat & Tears (song)|Blood Sweat & Tears]]\"{{ref|a|[a]}}{{Ref|c|[c]}} / \"[[Fire (BTS song)|Fire]]\"{{ref|b|[b]}}\n# \"Boy in Luv\"{{ref|a|[a]}}{{Ref|c|[c]}} / \"Silver Spoon\"{{ref|b|[b]}}\n# \"Danger\"{{ref|a|[a]}} / \"Dope\"{{ref|b|[b]}}/ \"Fire\"{{Ref|c|[c]}}\n# \"[[Airplane Pt. 2]]\"\n# \"[[Singularity (song)|Singularity]]\"\n# \"[[Fake Love (BTS song)|Fake Love]]\"\n# \"Trivia \u8f49: Seesaw\"\n# \"[[Epiphany (BTS song)|Epiphany]]\"\n# \"The Truth Untold\"\n# \"Outro: Tear\"\n# \"[[Mic Drop (song)|Mic Drop]]\"\n;Encore\n#<li value=25> \"So What\"\n# \"Anpanman\"\n# \"Answer: Love Myself\"\n\n{{Col-2}}\n'''Notes'''\n*{{sup|{{note|a|[a]}}}} indicates setlist one\n*{{sup|{{note|b|[b]}}}}indicates setlist two\n*{{Sup|{{note|c|[c]}}}}indicates setlist three\n{{ col end }}\n\n== Tour dates ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|- \"\n! width=\"175\" | Date\n! width=\"150\" | City\n! width=\"150\" | Country\n! width=\"275\" | Venue\n! width=\"200\" | Attendance\n! width=\"150\" | Revenue \n|-\n! colspan=\"6\"| '''Leg 1 \u2013 Asia'''\n|-\n|August 25, 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Seoul]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |South Korea\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Seoul Olympic Stadium]]\t\n| rowspan=\"2\" |90,000 / 90,000<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|script-title=ko:\"80\ub9cc \ud32c, \uae30\ub2e4\ub824\uc694\"\u2026\uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \ub300\uc7a5\uc815 \ub098\uc11c\ub294 \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=001&aid=0010277340|website=naver.com|language=ko-kr|accessdate=August 18, 2018}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\t$8,411,739<!-- Converted 9.45 billion won to USD--><ref name=\":1\"/>\n|-\n|August 26, 2018\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" | '''Leg 2 \u2013 North America''' \n|-\n|September 5, 2018\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Los Angeles]]\n| rowspan=\"7\" |United States\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Staples Center]]\n| rowspan=\"14\" |180,000 / 180,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20180603000223|title=BTS world tour sold out|last=Shim|first=Woo-hyun|date=June 3, 2018|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=February 22, 2019}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"15\" {{n/a}} \n|-\n|September 6, 2018\n|-\n|September 8, 2018\n|-\n|September 9, 2018\n|-\n|September 12, 2018\n|[[Oakland, California]]\n|[[Oracle Arena]