 19, 2019}}</ref>\n| $2,250,000<ref name=\"pollstar\"/>\n|-\n|October 16, 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Berlin]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Germany\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Mercedes-Benz Arena (Berlin)|Mercedes-Benz Arena]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |30,000 / 30,000<ref name=\":1\"/>\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n|October 17, 2018\n|-\n|October 19, 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Paris]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |France\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[AccorHotels Arena]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |28,149 / 28,149<ref name=\"pollstar\"/>\n| rowspan=\"2\" | $4,580,000<ref name=\"pollstar\"/>\n|-\n|October 20, 2018\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\"| '''Leg 4 \u2013 Asia'''\n|-\n|November 13, 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Tokyo]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" |Japan\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Tokyo Dome]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 380,000 / 380,000{{efn|name=Japan|The score data is combined from the shows held in Japan from November 13, 14, 21, 23, 24, January 12, 13, February 16, & 17 respectively.}}<ref name = \"Japan\">{{cite web|script-title=ja:BTS\uff08\u9632\u5f3e\u5c11\u5e74\u56e3\uff09\u300111\u6708\u3088\u308a\u521d\u306e\u65e5\u672c\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u30fb\u30c4\u30a2\u30fc\u300cBTS WORLD TOUR 'LOVE YOURSELF'\uff5eJAPAN EDITION\uff5e\u300d\u958b\u50ac|url=https://tower.jp/article/news/2018/07/31/tg007|website=Tower Records Japan|accessdate=October 16, 2018|date=July 31, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"5\"| $44,477,061<!--\u20a950 billion was converted to USD-->{{efn|name=Japan sales|Sales are combined from the shows held in Japan from November 13, 14, 21, 23, 24, January 12, 13, February 16, & 17 respectively.}}<ref>{{cite web |title=\u65e5 \uc5f4\ub3c4 \uc0ac\ub85c\uc7a1\uc740 \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8\u202638\ub9cc\uba85 \uc5f4\uad11|url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=015&aid=0004094563&sid1=001|website=[[Naver (corporation)|Naver]]|publisher=Hankyung News|accessdate=February 17, 2019|language=Korean|date=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|November 14, 2018\n|-\n|November 21, 2018\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Osaka]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Kyocera Dome Osaka]]\n|-\n|November 23, 2018\n|-\n|November 24, 2018\n|-\n|December 8, 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Taoyuan, Taiwan|Taoyuan]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Taiwan\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Taoyuan International Baseball Stadium]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|250,000 / 250,000{{efn|name=Asia|The score data is combined from the shows held in Asia from December 8, 9, January 19, March 20, 21, 23, 24, April 6, & 7 respectively.}}<ref>{{cite web|title=BTS to wrap up world tour in Thailand|url=https://en.yna.co.kr/view/AEN20190407001400315|website=[[Yonhap]]|accessdate=April 7, 2019|date=April 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |$7,111,720<!--NT$220 million was converted to USD--><ref name=\"TW\">{{cite web|script-title=zh:\u9632\u5f48\u5c11\u5e74\u5718\u6392\u5b57\u9001ARMY\u3000\u544a\u767d\u300c\u53f0\u7063\u5c31\u50cf\u5bb6\u300d|url=https://tw.entertainment.appledaily.com/realtime/20181208/1480370/|website=TW Entertainment|accessdate=December 8, 2018|language=zh-hant|date=December 8, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|December 9, 2018\n|-\n|January 12, 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Nagoya]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Japan\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Nagoya Dome]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{efn|name=Japan}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{efn|name=Japan sales}}\n|-\n|January 13, 2019\n|-\n|January 19, 2019\n| colspan=\"2\" | [[Singapore]]\n| [[Singapore National Stadium]]\n| {{efn|name=Asia}}\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|February 16, 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Fukuoka]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Japan\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Fukuoka Yahuoku! Dome]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{efn|name=Japan}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{efn|name=Japan sales}}\n|-\n|February 17, 2019\n|-\n|March 20, 2019\n| rowspan=\"4\" colspan=\"2\" |[[Hong Kong]]\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[AsiaWorld\u2013Expo]]\n| rowspan=\"4\"|{{efn|name=Asia}}\n| rowspan=\"6\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n|March 21, 2019\n|-\n|March 23, 2019\n|-\n|March 24, 2019\n|-\n|April 6, 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Bangkok]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Thailand\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Rajamangala National Stadium]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{efn|name=Asia}}\n|-\n|April 7, 2019\n|-\n! colspan=4|'''Total'''\n! 1,043,517 / 1,044,320 (99.9%)\n! $71,773,660\n|}\n\n== Speak Yourself extension ==\n{{short description|concert tour by BTS}}\n{{Infobox concert tour|concert_tour_name=BTS World Tour Love Yourself: Speak Yourself|image=BTS World Tour Love Yourself Speak Yourself logo.png|landscape=yes|image_caption=|artist=[[BTS (band)|BTS]]|type=extended|album=''[[Map of the Soul: Persona]]''|start_date={{date|2019-05-04|MDY}}|end_date={{date|2019-10-29|MDY}}|number_of_legs=4|number_of_shows={{unbulleted list|8 in Asia|2 in South America|6 in North America|4 in Europe|20 in total}}|last_tour=BTS World Tour: Love Yourself<br/>(2018-2019)|this_tour='''BTS World Tour Love Yourself: Speak Yourself'''<br/>(2019)|next_tour=[[Map of the Soul Tour|BTS Map of the Soul Tour]]<br/>(2020)|attendance=976,283|gross=$116 million}}\n\n=== Background ===\nBTS World Tour Love Yourself: Speak Yourself was the stadium extension to the Love Yourself World Tour, separated under a different name.<ref name=\"SYextension\">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bts/8498863/bts-add-2019-tour-dates|title=BTS Add Additional 2019 Stadium Tour Stops: See the New Dates|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Gab|last=Ginsberg|date=February 19, 2019|accessdate=March 28, 2019}}</ref> The extension began on May 4, 2019 in [[Pasadena, California]] and featured concerts in North and South America, Europe, and Asia, including the United States, Brazil, the United Kingdom, France, and Japan.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/caitlinkelley/2019/02/19/bts-announce-world-tour-love-yourself-speak-yourself/#2a2291da3622|title=BTS Announce Upcoming World Tour, 'Love Yourself: Speak Yourself'|work=[[Forbes]]|last=Kelley|first=Caitlin|date=February 19, 2019|accessdate=March 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nSpeak Yourself was first announced on February 19, 2019 through the [[Big Hit Entertainment]] [[YouTube]] channel, where a spot for the extension was posted. The video featured clips of the BTS members performing, with the title and dates for the tour written on top of them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r-uN2VzsfXU|title=BTS (\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8) World Tour 'Love Yourself: Speak Yourself' Spot|date=February 19, 2018|work=BigHit Entertainment|accessdate=February 19, 2018}}</ref> That same day, [[Live Nation]] was revealed as the concert promoter,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://musicmayhemmagazine.com/bts-announces-stadium-tour-dates-on-love-yourself-speak-yourself-world-tour/|title=BTS Announces Stadium Tour Dates on \u2018Love Yourself: Speak Yourself\u2019 World Tour|author=Music Mayhem|work=Music Mayhem Magazine|date=February 19, 2019|accessdate=March 12, 2019}}</ref> with tickets sold through [[Ticketmaster]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bts/8500687/bts-sell-out-love-yourself-speak-yourself-tour-dates|title=BTS Sell Out 'Love Yourself: Speak Yourself' Stadium Dates in England, France & U.S.|last=Herman|first=Tamar|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=March 1, 2019|accessdate=March 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Commercial reception ===\nIn North America, tickets sold out for all initial three dates in approximately two and a half hours.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bts/8500687/bts-sell-out-love-yourself-speak-yourself-tour-dates|title=BTS Sell Out 'Love Yourself: Speak Yourself' Stadium Dates in England, France & U.S.|last1=Herman|first1=Tamar|date=March 1, 2019|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 1, 2019}}</ref> The [[Wembley Stadium]] stop sold out in 90 minutes and in France tickets sold out in about five and a half hours.<ref name=\":2\"/> Tickets went on sale in Brazil on March 11, 2019. Despite ticket sales website having connecting issues at the time, tickets sold out in 75 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.news.naver.com/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=104&oid=001&aid=0010687745|title=BTS, \ube0c\ub77c\uc9c8 \uacf5\uc5f0 \uc785\uc7a5\uad8c \uc778\ud130\ub137 \ud310\ub9e4 75\ubd84\ub9cc\uc5d0 \ub9e4\uc9c4|date=March 12, 2019|website=[[Naver (corporation)|Naver]]|publisher=[[Yonhap News]]|language=Korean|accessdate=March 11, 2019}}</ref> To accommodate demand, additional dates were added to all American, European, and Brazilian dates.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bts/8500758/bts-tour-dates-love-yourself-speak-yourself-second-concerts-added|title=BTS Add Second 'Love Yourself: Speak Yourself' Stadium Shows in Europe, U.S. After First Dates Sell Out|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=March 2, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"brazild1\">{{cite news|url=http://popcrush.com/bts-tour-sales-beat-rolling-stones-cardi-b/|title=BTS Just Outsold Rolling Stones, Cardi B, Korn and Other Music Heavy Hitters|date=March 4, 2019|work=[[PopCrush]]|accessdate=March 6, 2019}}</ref> The additional European dates sold out the same day they were listed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/the-tweets-about-the-second-round-of-bts-speak-yourself-tour-tickets-are-like-deja-vu-16821808|title=The Tweets About The Second Round Of BTS' 'Speak Yourself' Tour Tickets Are Like Deja Vu|last=Martinez|first=Tara|date=March 8, 2019|work=[[Elite Daily]]|accessdate=March 12, 2019}}</ref> According to pop music website ''PopCrush'', the extension had higher first-day sales in the United States and Europe than [[the Rolling Stones]]' 2019 tour, which went on sale the same day.<ref name=\"brazild1\" /> BTS were also the first Asian act to sell out the [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|Rose Bowl]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.radio.com/blogs/tiana-timmerberg/bts-makes-history-first-asian-artist-ever-do|title=BTS Makes History as the First Asian Artist to Ever Do This|last=Timmerberg|first=Tiana|date=March 6, 2019|accessdate=March 12, 2019|website=[[Radio.com]]}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Boxscore, the North and South American leg of the tour generated $51.7 million in ticket sales and played to 384,498 fans over eight sold out shows, becoming the highest grossing concert tour in month of May 2019.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8517718/bts-surpasses-50-million-top-grossing-tour-may-2019|title=BTS Surpasses $50 Million in May with the Month's Top-Grossing Tour|date=June 27, 2019|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=June 27, 2019}}</ref> These included a two night stint at Chicago's [[Soldier Field]], playing for 88,156 people, and two nights at East Rutherford's [[MetLife Stadium|Met Life Stadium]], playing for 98,574.<ref name=\"SYE\" /> Grossing $16.6 million with an attendance of 113,040, Los Angeles' [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|Rose Bowl]] was the highest grossing show of the leg and the tour overall, ranking as the sixth largest boxscore of the year reported by ''Billboard''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/bryanrolli/2019/12/06/bts-were-the-top-grossing-touring-group-of-2019/#742108196199|title=BTS Were The Top-Grossing Touring Group Of 2019|last=|first=|date=2019-12-06|website=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-07}}</ref> BTS' Rose Bowl stint was also the single highest-grossing engagement in the venue's Boxscore history, out-pacing previous high marks by [[Taylor Swift]] and [[U2]], as well as co-headlining stints by [[Beyonc\u00e9]] & [[Jay-Z]] and [[Eminem]] & [[Rihanna]].<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8516047/bts-600000-tickets-six-markets-love-yourself-speak-yourself-tour|title=BTS Moves 600,000 Tickets in 6 Markets on the Love Yourself: Speak Yourself Tour|last1=Frankenberg|first1=Eric|date=June 14, 2019|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2019}}</ref> In Europe, the tour continued to be a success with two sold out nights at London's [[Wembley Stadium]], playing for 114,583 people, and two nights at Paris' [[Stade de France]], playing to a crowd of 107,328.<ref name=\"SYE\" /> Combined, the first 12 shows of the tour extension grossed $78.9 million with 606,409 tickets.<ref name=\":3\" /> \n\nAveraging $5.8 million and 48,814 tickets per show, the tour extension's total gross revenue reached $115,749,851 with total attendance topping out at 976,283 tickets.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8543647/bts-love-yourself-speak-tour-earnings|title=BTS Finish Love Yourself: Speak Yourself Tour With $116 Million|last=|first=|date=2019-11-14|website=Billboard|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-16}}</ref> BTS, with the Love Yourself World Tour, were the top-grossing touring group of 2019 and ranked at number 3 on ''Billboard's'' Year End Top 40 Tours. With $196.4 million from 1.6 million tickets at 42 shows in 2019, BTS holds the highest year end ranking in ''Billboard'' Boxscore history for an act that performs primarily in a non-English language.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8545427/ed-sheeran-rolling-stones-2019-touring-charts|title=The Year in Touring Charts 2019: Ed Sheeran Meets The Rolling Stones in Boxscore History|last=Frankenburg|first=Eric|date=2019-12-05|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-20}}</ref> ''[[Pollstar]]''<nowiki/>'s Year End Top 100 Tours chart ranked BTS at number 6.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pollstar.com/Chart/2019/12/Top100%20WorldwideTours_790.pdf|title=2019 Year End Charts Top 100 Worldwide Tours|website=[[Pollstar]]|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref> On ''Billboard''<nowiki/>'s Year End Top 25 Boxscores, BTS held seven entries.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nTheir three day finale in Seoul in October 2019 was estimated to have an economic value of almost \u20a91 trillion ($862 million) and brought in 187,000 foreign visitors to South Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/article/001/0011291173|title=\ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8 \uc11c\uc6b8 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \uacbd\uc81c\ud6a8\uacfc 1\uc870\uc6d0 \uc721\ubc15|last=Rambo|first=|date=2019-12-22|website=Yonhap news|language=ko|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-22}}</ref>\n\n==Setlists==\nBTS featured this list for all dates of their concert extension.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kelley|first1=Caitlin|title=BTS bring eye-popping visuals, props, and reworked songs to Love Yourself: Speak Yourself tour opener |url=https://ew.com/concerts/2019/05/05/bts-love-yourself-speak-yourself-tour-review/|website=Entertainment Weekly|accessdate=May 7, 2019|date=May 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Col-start}}\n{{Col-2}}\n'''Love Yourself: Speak Yourself setlist'''\n# \"[[Dionysus (song)|Dionysus]]\"\n# \"[[Not Today (BTS song)|Not Today]]\"\n# \"Outro: Wings\"\n# \"Trivia: Just Dance\"\n# \"[[Euphoria (BTS song)|Euphoria]]\"\n# \"Best of Me\"\n# \"[[Serendipity (BTS song)|Serendipity]]\"\n# \"Trivia: Love\"\n# \"[[Boy With Luv]]\"\n# \"Dope\"\n# \"Silver Spoon\"\n# \"[[Fire (BTS song)|Fire]]\"\n# \"[[Idol (BTS song)|Idol]]\"\n# \"[[Singularity (song)|Singularity]]\"\n# \"[[Fake Love (BTS song)|Fake Love]]\" (Rocking Vibe Remix)\n# \"Trivia: Seesaw\"\n# \"[[Epiphany (BTS song)|Epiphany]]\"\n# \"The Truth Untold\"\n# \"Outro: Tear\"\n# \"[[Mic Drop (song)|Mic Drop]]\"\n;Encore\n#<li value=21>\"Anpanman\"\n# \"So What\"\n# \"[[Make It Right (BTS song)|Make It Right]]\"\n# \"Mikrokosmos\"\n</ol>\n{{Div col end}}\n\n{{Col-2}}\n'''Love Yourself: Speak Yourself: The Final setlist'''\n# \"[[Dionysus (song)|Dionysus]]\"\n# \"[[Not Today (BTS song)|Not Today]]\"\n# \"Outro: Wings\"\n# \"Trivia: Just Dance\"\n# \"[[Euphoria (BTS song)|Euphoria]]\"\n# \"Best of Me\"\n# \"[[Serendipity (BTS song)|Serendipity]]\"\n# \"Trivia: Love\"\n# \"[[Boy With Luv]]\"\n# \"Dope\"\n# \"Silver Spoon\"\n# \"[[Fire (BTS song)|Fire]]\"\n# \"[